Tensions escalated in Baluchistan as armed Bugti tribesmen clashed with paramilitary forces near Dera Bugti, leading to casualties and injuries.
The rebels, demanding autonomy and increased benefits, ambushed a military convoy, sparking fierce gun battles.
The violence surged after a doctor's rape near the Sui gasfield, with bomb blasts and temple destruction adding to the chaos.
Thousands evacuated the area amid fears of further clashes, as the government filed cases against tribal leaders.
The region remains volatile, with ongoing tribal revolts and security concerns.
